The "gem5-mcpat" script implement multiple commands. You can see a description
of each by passing them the "--help" argument.

Template generation uses the jinja framework (http://jinja.pocoo.org), and
requires version 2.7 or later.

In a Debian or Ubuntu system, you can install it with:

    sudo apt-get install python-jinja2

To check the available versions:

    sudo apt-cache policy python-jinja2

You can also install jinja locally using virtualenv and pip:

    sudo apt-get install virtualenv
    virtualenv --system-site-packages ~/local-jinja
    . ~/local-jinja/bin/activate
    pip install "jinja2>=2.7"

Just remember to activate your virtualenv before using template generation, so
that your local jinja installation is available:

    . ~/local-jinja/bin/activate
    /path/to/gem5-mcpat/gem5-mcpat ...
